\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Empirical Moran scatter for the Chongqing matched pre-treatment residual (standardised residual on the $x$-axis, its spatial lag on the $y$-axis). The slope is the empirical Moran's $I = 0.112$, statistically significant under 99 permutations ($p=0.01$); under the default 0.10 rule it triggers a material residual-spatial caution, while under a high-specificity 0.20 sensitivity threshold it would be recorded as significant-below-material.}}{15}{figure.caption.13}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:residual}{{5}{15}{Empirical Moran scatter for the Chongqing matched pre-treatment residual (standardised residual on the $x$-axis, its spatial lag on the $y$-axis). The slope is the empirical Moran's $I = 0.112$, statistically significant under 99 permutations ($p=0.01$); under the default 0.10 rule it triggers a material residual-spatial caution, while under a high-specificity 0.20 sensitivity threshold it would be recorded as significant-below-material}{figure.caption.13}{}}
